de.sub.goobi.helper.tasks

Class EmptyTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • de.sub.goobi.helper.tasks.EmptyTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    INameableTask, Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CreateNewspaperProcessesTask, ExportDmsTask, ExportNewspaperBatchTask, ExportSerialBatchTask, LongRunningTask, TaskScriptThread

    public class EmptyTask
extends Thread
implements INameableTask
    The class EmptyTask is the base class for worker threads that operate independently to do the work in the background. The name empty task points out that the task doesn’t do anything sensible yet. It is here to be extended.
    Author:
    Matthias Ronge <matthias.ronge@zeutschel.de>

      • CATCH_ALL

        public static final Thread.UncaughtExceptionHandler CATCH_ALL
        The constant CATCH_ALL holds an UncaughtExceptionHandler implementation which will automatically be attached to all task threads. Otherwise exceptions might get lost or even bring the runtime to crash.

      • setException

        public void setException(Throwable exception)
        The procedure setException can be used to save an exception that occurred and show it in the front end. It will only record the first exception (which is likely to be the source of all the misery) and it will not record an InterruptedException if the thread has already been interrupted.
        Parameters:
        exception - exception to save

      • setNameDetail

        protected void setNameDetail(String detail)
        The procedure setNameDetail() may be used to set the task’s name along with a detail that doesn’t require translation and is helpful when being shown in the front end (such as the name of the entity the task is based on). The name detail should be set once (in the constructor). You may pass in null to reset the name and remove the detail.

        I.e., if your task is about creation of OCR for a process, the detail here could be the process title.

        Parameters:
        detail - a name detail, may be null

      • setWorkDetail

        public void setWorkDetail(String detail)
        The procedure setWorkDetail() may be used to set some detail information that don’t require translation and are helpful when being shown in the front end (such as the name of the entity that is currently being processed by the task). The name detail should be set every time the progress is determined. You may pass in null to remove the detail.

        I.e., if your task is about creation of OCR for a process, the detail here could be the image file being processed right now.

        Parameters:
        detail - a work detail, may be null

      • start

        public void start()
        Causes this thread to begin execution; the Java Virtual Machine will create a standalone thread and call the run method of this class. The result is that two threads are running concurrently: the current thread which returns from the call to the start method, and the other thread which executes its run method. In addition, this method override ensures that the thread is properly registered in the task manager and that its uncaught exception handler has been properly set.
        Overrides:
        start in class Thread
        See Also:
        Thread.start()
